  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-03-17",
    "date": "2022-03-22T13:24:35Z",
    "text": "Cost of War Act of 2022\n\nThis bill directs the Department of Defense (DOD) to post on its public website information relating to the cost to U.S. taxpayers of any overseas contingency operation conducted by the U.S. Armed Forces on or after September 18, 2001. DOD must update such information not later than 90 days after the end of each fiscal year."
